name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Mr. Ray was one of the good guys in this business. In fact, he was just one of the good guys, period. RIP.  https://t.co/iKgzZYPZyI

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: “For unto us a Child is born, unto us a Son is given; and the government shall be upon His shoulder. And His name shall be called Wonderful, Counselor, The Mighty God, The Everlasting Father, The Prince of Peace.” Isaiah 9:6   Merry Christmas from the Reeves Family!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: On Christmas Eve, I am grateful for my family, my friends, and the people of Mississippi. I hope that you have a very Merry Christmas. Please stay safe and may God bless us all!  https://t.co/w7PRduksuR

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: This morning, I signed an executive order extending our mask rules to all counties that qualify—which is now every county except four very small ones. We all need to be extra aware. You know what to do! Protect yourself and your family. Stay safe, and Merry Christmas!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Elee and I got to bring a little cheer to kids in Mississippi’s Children’s Hospital, delivering gift bags for their families this morning.   The First Lady led the effort! Honored to have a partner in leadership with such a heart for the people we work for.  https://t.co/366wt3ljPT

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Thank you for all the gifts that you have given us. Thank you for making us Mississippians and Americans—giving us that community. Thank you for being a good Father to us all. Amen.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please help us to do your will, not lean on our own understanding, acknowledge you in all things, and allow you to make our path straight without our arrogant resistance.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please grant wisdom to elected officials, business leaders, pastors, teachers, parents, and everyone else who has been asked to make tough decisions with no playbook in this time.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please allow Christmas—your day—to be a time of togetherness, while protecting families from infection and granting everyone the wisdom to try and make their events safe.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please reward and look after those workers and volunteers who have stepped up to serve their fellow Mississippians in this unique point in history.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please give community and fellowship to anyone struggling with loneliness. Please give joy and purpose to those struggling with depression. Please help all Mississippians to understand that they are loved and needed—even if they don’t feel it all the time.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please protect those who are struggling with lost homes or hurting businesses as a result of the pandemic or other natural disasters. Please give pride of work, security of resources, and support from all around.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Please bring peace and love to those who have lost family members and loved ones this year.   Please grant strength and your supernatural protection to anyone fighting to stay healthy or recover today.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: First, thank you, God, for your love and grace. We would be lost without it. Please help us to extend the same to others. Even in this time of fear, stress, and disagreement.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Today is Mississippi’s statewide day of Prayer, Humility, and Fasting. We can come together on Facebook Live today at 5:00 PM. I also wanted to start the day in prayer that you may be able to join me in.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Elee and I are deeply saddened by the loss of former Gov. William Winter. He truly loved this state and his country. And the people of Mississippi loved him back. He will be missed by all of us.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Tomorrow is our statewide Day of Prayer, Humility, and Fasting. In times of distress, we go to the Lord. There is power in prayer. If you are willing, please join us at 5 on Facebook Live to pray.   “Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears us up; God is our salvation.” Psalm 68:19

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Today at 10:30, on Facebook Live, I will be signing a proclamation to designate this Sunday as a statewide Day of Prayer, Humility, and Fasting. Please join us for that announcement if you are willing, and set aside some extra time on Sunday to pray for the future of our state.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Interesting debate... I get endless posts from skeptics like “If you want us to take the vaccine, why won’t you take it?”  I’m ready—but don’t want to be accused of cutting in line. What do you think is the better action by leaders? Show confidence or let others get access first?

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Psalm 107:28-31  “Then they cried to the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress. He made the storm be still, and the waves of the sea were hushed. Then they were glad that the waters were quiet, and he brought them to their desired haven.”

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: There are still some logistical hurdles left regarding the vaccine, but I am incredibly optimistic and encouraged. We can see light at the end of the tunnel. We just have to push and make it there. A safe vaccine is a tremendous answer to prayer.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: This is month ten of the virus. We’re going on nearly 300 days to slow the spread. We’re all fed up and angry. But with grace, we can make it through. We can do the little things for a little while longer. You don’t have to be perfect in order to make a difference, just try.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Once anyone who wants a vaccine has access to it, we should be able to return to life as we knew it. People can reasonably protect themselves. I’ll be eager to have a vaccine as soon as it’s appropriate. I’m confident in it, and I’m ready to move on.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: The first COVID vaccine has been administered in MS! It’s a historic American accomplishment. If all goes perfectly (which is rare in 2020 but let’s pray) we may be able to distribute about as many vaccines in Mississippi over the next month as we have total COVID cases now.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Mississippi electors just officially cast the state’s ballots for Donald J. Trump. A safe and fair election here in Mississippi—not upended by last-minute schemes to radically alter voting methods. Election integrity is vital.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Great news, Mr. Chairman! Let’s get it done! Boldly lowering taxes can break down the door to economic deals that would transform our economy!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Rest In Peace to Charley Pride, a Mississippi great.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Amen, Mr. Chairman! This is the moment to make a bold move and get competitive for jobs and capital by eliminating the income tax. We can have an impact for generations.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Excited for @DougDucey and @KimReynoldsIA leadership at the RGA, and to serve with @BillLeeTN in helping support conservative policy for governors across the country! Thank you to my fellow governors for trusting me with this role.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Today is the anniversary of Pearl Harbor—a solemn reminder that Americans will always be threatened by enemies of freedom and that brave men and women will rally to defend and avenge our sacred country.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Christmas at the Governor’s Mansion is very different this year. No large crowds to see the decorations—social distancing & masks. Elee wanted to do a special Facebook Live to show everybody what she put together at the people’s house! Join at 2 here:  https://t.co/PxeRxY8mWA

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: COVID-19 continues to rage throughout the country and here in Mississippi. Please be extra cautious and mindful during this time. We will have an update on our EO later this week—in the meantime the best tool is the same: wear a mask. Avoid crowds. Be smart. Protect loved ones.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Mississippi was hit hard by Hurricane Zeta. Recovery is never fast, but the team has leapt into action to protect those hit hardest. We cannot forget about this critical mission, even as we deal with other crises. More in today’s briefing at 2:30.  https://t.co/CxTtySG65e

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Leach vs. Kiffin 2 really good coaches 2 great Universities  ONE Golden Egg   Records don’t matter. Last year doesn’t matter. Just 60 minutes for the trophy!  Who you think gets bragging rights and the Egg for the next year?? #EggBowl

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I’m truly thankful for Mississippi. I know that we can continue to push through, keep our heads high, rejoice in our blessings, pray continually, and give thanks. God bless. Please stay safe today.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I’m thankful for a community of Mississippians who have come together this year to look after one another and treat each other with love. I’ve been in some office or another for awhile now. In my first year as Governor, I’ve never felt closer to the people I work for.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I’m thankful for a renewed faith that comes with hard times. When things get rough, you run to your savior. And he’s always there.   I’m thankful for my family—all the joy, banter, sports, school, elation, frustration—everything is a blessing.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: It’s been a year to dwell on the negative, bringing prayer requests for grace and mercy to God. Today, even despite the circumstances, we can come to God with joy and give thanks, just as he instructs us to do.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: “Rejoice always, pray continually, give thanks in all circumstances; for this is God’s will for you in Christ Jesus.” -1 Thessalonians 5:16-18

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I am so blessed to have a rock-steady partner, loving friend, and incredible Mom to our girls by my side through all of our family’s adventures. Happy 19th Anniversary, Elee! God has truly blessed me with you.  https://t.co/B5NOPFSfUo

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I have a call with HHS officials today at 2:00 to discuss the progress on vaccines and our distribution plan and strategy. So, I’ll see you at 2:30 tomorrow with an update on our fight against Covid! Stay safe. Please wear a mask. Small groups. Social distancing.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Congratulations to Chief Justice Randolph, Presiding Justice King, Justice Coleman, and Justice Griffis on your victories this year! We certified the election results this morning. And thank you to @MichaelWatsonMS and @LynnFitchAG for your work to ensure election integrity.  https://t.co/4g1wNxsqQF

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Thank you, Jim! Prayer is a powerful force!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: A Mississippian that makes $40,000 in taxable income would save nearly $2,000 with the income tax eliminated. It would be huge for business, retirees, and workers. This should be the starting point for any tax discussion in the legislature this year: cut taxes, don’t raise them.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Eliminate the Income Tax!   Right now, the global economy is chaotic. We have the chance to attract investment and high-paying jobs. We need to produce more products here, and grow our population. We need to make a bold move to capitalize on the growth possibilities.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Investments in K-12 Education: multi-million dollar investments in teachers, math coaches, and workforce development courses that can help Mississippi’s students learn a trade and earn higher wages.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Patriotic Education Fund: create a program that funds teaching that reminds the next generation that America is the greatest nation in history. Democracy, capitalism, and other American values are under attack—from foreign and domestic influences. We need to push back.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Protecting Small Businesses: 2,400 grants of $5,000 to jump start small businesses that were closed during the height of the pandemic.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Funding the Police: investing $3 million in law enforcement officer training to Back the Blue and ensure that they have the confidence of the community.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Today, I released our Executive Budget Recommendation, and this budget funds several key priorities that I want to share:

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Today at 2:30, I plan to host a Facebook Live update on Coronavirus in Mississippi and release our Executive Budget proposal—key priorities are eliminating the income tax, funding the police, and strengthening education. Details on that and more. Join if you can!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Watch for college coaches wearing the @CoachToCureMD logo today & pitch in to help fight this lethal childhood disorder by texting CURE to 501501. Let's help @wernerladderco & @WeAreAFCA #TackleDuchenne Muscular Dystrophy.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Planning to do a Facebook Live at 2:30...focus will be on COVID-19 (across the state and in my own family.) As cases rise, please take the threat seriously. None of us want to be responsible for spreading this disease to our most vulnerable loved ones.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Excited to have Bailey on board—she will do a great job!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Thank you to the brave men and women who serve our country in uniform. Your service and sacrifice is a model to us all. Happy Veterans Day!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: This virus is very contagious and it is not gone—please be careful, stay safe and wear a mask!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Quick update: Elee and our other girls tested negative again. So did I. Since Maddie also had a negative test as recently as yesterday we’re going to monitor closely and be cautious. I’ve heard and felt the outpouring of prayers, and they mean the world to Maddie and all of us!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I want to share a prayer request. My youngest daughter just tested positive for COVID-19. She feels OK, but could still use prayers! Please pray for her momma too!  Our entire family will be getting tested again and isolating for the time being. Stay safe, and God bless!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Congratulations to Booneville’s own Asya Branch—the new Miss USA! Emma was excited to see your win, and we are all honored to have you representing our state. You make Mississippi proud!  https://t.co/dzzoayDMCv

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: This is despicable. Playing politics to prevent a life-saving vaccine from being distributed because he’s jealous that the Trump administration got us here. If liberal states stiff-arm a safe vaccine, Mississippi will be first in line to give our citizens the option.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: But based on what I see in other states today, I will also do everything in my power to make sure universal mail-in voting and no-excuse early voting are not allowed in MS—not while I’m governor! Too much chaos. Only way it’d happen is if many GOP legislators override a veto!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I will do everything in my power to ensure every ballot legally cast in the 2020 election in Mississippi gets counted—no matter how long it takes.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: We voted (in Hinds County for the first time since our 20’s!) Long—but fast moving—lines. Super nice people with lots of different political opinions. Safe and secure.   It fills me with pride for state and country every time. We LOVE Mississippi...today, tomorrow, and forever!  https://t.co/HwdSSzjmvb

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Polls are open across Mississippi. I hope that you will exercise your right to vote. Not all generations had it. Many in the world still don’t today.   Your vote matters. When you speak with that ballot, the most powerful people in the world are forced to listen. Enjoy it.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Polls are OPEN. Vote Mississippi. Vote like the future of our country depends on it!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Thank you to MEMA, National Guard, local EMA’s, UMCOR, Jackson Co Baptists, MPCO, Red Cross, Salvation Army, MS Baptist Disaster Response, God’s Pit Crew, Eight Days of Hope, lineworkers... Way too many more Good Samaritans to name—know some missed here. Inspiring work!

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: We’ve distributed 36,426 tarps to more than 9,000 homes. More than 220,000 meals and 360,000 bottles of water. We still have a few Mississippians in shelters. Damage assessments are going on now—to make sure Mississippi families, businesses, and infrastructure can rebuild.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: We originally had 220,000 customers who lost power. That’s a massive logistical effort to fix. Today, 193,095 customers have had power restored. More work to do there—teams are tirelessly clearing damage and working to restore.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Hurricane Zeta was one of the more destructive storms we’ve had to face in a while. Thank God for the unbeatable spirit and capable service of Mississippians. The response is ongoing. It doesn’t end when the storm moves through. Here’s a data-based update:

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Don’t be overly optimistic or dejected based on polling! Just get out and vote for what you believe in! That’s your right as an American, and no narrative should persuade you to believe it doesn’t matter.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: In every one of my campaigns, we have had three clear beliefs on polling: 1- Never pay for a poll you don’t believe; 2- Never believe a poll you don’t pay for; 3- The only poll that ultimately matters is the one taken on Election Day.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Polling... I believe in polling—when done right!  But for those focused on national polling today, I’d encourage you to zoom out and look at the bigger picture! Whoever funds and runs the poll has many built-in assumptions and ways to manipulate the data.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: There are good folks on all sides of the medical marijuana debate. Most non-stoners say we should be careful & deliberate. Initiative 65 is the opposite. Experts say it would mean the most liberal weed rules in the US! Pot shops everywhere—no local authority. Voting against both.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: On this the final Sabbath before Election Day in America, please join Elee and me in praying to a loving God to provide guidance and direction for all those yet to vote and for protection and healing of our nation no matter the outcome.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: 2020 has been tough on so many. One group constantly targeted for political attacks has been our proud police men and women. Imagine how proud I was when my little one told me what she wanted to be for Halloween!  https://t.co/fXAGVHHdrF

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Mississippi got hit hard by Hurricane Zeta last night. One thing I know about Mississippians: when we get hit hard, we get up. We come together and rebuild. I will be on the coast this afternoon to be a part of that effort—joining an army of emergency operators and volunteers.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Just spoke with @realDonaldTrump and he expressed his full support for the people of Mississippi as we deal with the fallout of Zeta. Anything we need in this emergency, he’ll get it to us. Grateful for a President who is never off the clock—working hard to protect Americans.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: President Trump just approved Mississippi’s Hurricane Zeta emergency declaration. Swift, decisive action that will enable us to get through and rebuild.   Please continue to stay alert and pray.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: Take cover. Stay smart. Emergency operators are prepared to respond.

name: Tate Reeves
tweet: I’ve signed an emergency declaration in advance of Hurricane Zeta. Watch the weather. Be prepared.   Emergency operators are working to get ready for storm surge and hard winds—up to 9 feet of surge and winds up to 100 MPH. Stay sharp, stay safe, and pray for God’s protection.
